post_text: Does your child receive free or reduced-price school meals during the school year, or do you believe you may now qualify based on a recent income change? Pandemic-EBT, or P-EBT, can help you feed your family while schools are closed. You will receive a card with approximately $279 per eligible child that you can use to purchase food at stores that accept EBT. If you already receive SNAP benefits and are eligible for P-EBT, these funds will automatically load into your existing account. If you do not currently receive SNAP benefits, apply here for P-EBT today: https://www.colorado.gov/cdhs/p-ebt

post_text: Mrs. O'Dell, 6th grade teacher at Byers Elementary, applied for a grant through Colorado Parks and Wildlife and received all the money to fund a National Archery in Schools Program (NASP) at our school. Her class is our first to try it out and we hope to expand the program in the coming school year. Lucinda Gurley and Shatzie Wardall attended the training and are also certified NASP instructors for the the school.

post_text: The Byers Jr. and Sr. High School recently held a canned food drive to donate to families in need through the Cares Food bank of Strasburg. Students collected cans in their zero hour classes over the course of two weeks for the chance to win a pizza party and bragging rights. Students then blocked in their teachers' doors, the class with the most cans covering their teacher's door won. The winning class was was Mr. Thomas and Mrs. Pelton's zero hour class with 125 items. In total the Byers Jr. and Sr. High was able to donate over 780 non-perishable food items. Way to go Bulldogs!

post_text:
Dear Elementary Parents,
This Wednesday, Oct. 31st, will be our annual Halloween Parade and Party. We will be having a regular day of school up until it is time to change into costumes, so no need to come early. If you aren't helping your child change, you can head straight down to the big gym to find a seat to view the parade.

2:00-2:15 Time to change into costumes for the parade
2:15ish We will announce one class at a time to walk down to the gym for the parade.
2:35ish Classes and party parents will return to classrooms for parties. Everyone else is free to go. (Please just PARTY PARENTS at the parties. We need room to play games and there will only be enough snacks for the students. Thanks!)

PLEASE NOTE: If your child is doing something different at the end of the day (i.e. going with a friend, riding a different bus, etc.), we will need a note.

Thanks for helping us keep our kids safe!!

post_text:
Congratulations to the Byers boys and girls track teams on a great season. Austin Davis won the State Championship in the 110 High Hurdles and was runner-up in the High Jump. Austin Davis, James Linnebur, Wyatt Smith, and Edgar Garcia Medina placed 8th in the 800 Relay.

Shannon Sutliff was 7th in the 400 Meters. Shannon Sutliff, Lauren Marin, Becca Earl, and Janette Hernandez placed 7th in the 800 Relay. Amanda MacDonald, Lauren Marin, Kelsie Simpson, Becca Earl, and Shannon Sutliff placed 8th in the 800 Medley.

Congratulations also to the girls for setting a new school record in the 800 Relay and to Austin for setting a new school record in the high hurdles.
text:
Congratulations to the Byers boys and girls track teams on a great season. Austin Davis won the State Championship in the 110 High Hurdles and was runner-up in the High Jump. Austin Davis, James Linnebur, Wyatt Smith, and Edgar Garcia Medina placed 8th in the 800 Relay.

Shannon Sutliff was 7th in the 400 Meters. Shannon Sutliff, Lauren Marin, Becca Earl, and Janette Hernandez placed 7th in the 800 Relay. Amanda MacDonald, Lauren Marin, Kelsie Simpson, Becca Earl, and Shannon Sutliff placed 8th in the 800 Medley.

Congratulations also to the girls for setting a new school record in the 800 Relay and to Austin for setting a new school record in the high hurdles.

post_text:
Byers Kindergarten Roundup/Registration

The Byers Elementary Kindergarten Roundup/Registration will be May 22, 2018, for students new to Byers School District. If your child was enrolled in Byers Preschool Program you do not need to attend the roundup. Please call the Byers Elementary @ (303) 822-5292, ext. 1140 to make an appointment for the roundup. On roundup day you will need to bring your child’s birth certificate, immunization records, proof of residency (something with your name and address), and your child! Kindergarten students must be five years of age by June 1, 2013.
Preschool registration will be on May 16, 2018. Please call the Byers Elementary @ (303) 822-5292, ext. 1140 to make an appointment for the roundup. On roundup day you will need to bring your child’s birth certificate, immunization record, proof of residency (something with your name and address), and your child. Preschool students must be 3 years old by June 1, 2015, and 4 years old by June 1, 2014.
